---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Traditional Clothing" description="Explore Chinese traditional clothing - hanfu, cheongsam, silk embroidery, and the elegant fashion of 5,000 years of civilization.">
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-600 via-rose-600 to-pink-700 text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <span class="text-pink-200 text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase">Clothing</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mt-2 mb-4">Traditional Clothing</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-pink-100">From the flowing robes of Hanfu to the elegant cheongsam, Chinese fashion reflects millennia of craftsmanship and aesthetic philosophy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/clothing/hanfu" class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">👘</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2 group-hover:text-pink-600 transition-colors">Hanfu</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">The traditional clothing of the Han Chinese—wide sleeves, crossed collars, and elegant flowing lines.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clothing/cheongsam" class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🥻</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2 group-hover:text-pink-600 transition-colors">Cheongsam / Qipao</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">The iconic fitted dress that became a symbol of Chinese femininity worldwide.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clothing/embroidery" class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🧵</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2 group-hover:text-pink-600 transition-colors">Embroidery</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">The four famous embroidery styles: Su, Xiang, Shu, and Yue—each region with its own mastery.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clothing/silk" class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🐛</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2 group-hover:text-pink-600 transition-colors">Silk</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">The fabric that changed world history—China's 5,000-year secret finally revealed.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-8">Featured Articles</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <article class="group">
          <div class="aspect-video bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-400 to-rose-600 rounded-xl mb-4 flex items-center justify-center text-5xl">👘</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">What is Hanfu? A Beginner's Guide</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Understanding the history, styles, and modern revival of traditional Chinese clothing.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="group">
          <div class="aspect-video bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-400 to-pink-600 rounded-xl mb-4 flex items-center justify-center text-5xl">🪡</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">The Four Great Chinese Embroidery Styles</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Delicate needlework that transformed fabric into art over centuries.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="group">
          <div class="aspect-video bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-300 to-yellow-500 rounded-xl mb-4 flex items-center justify-center text-5xl">🏵️</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">The Silk Road: Fashion Connection</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">How Chinese silk dressed the Roman Empire and beyond.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
